title: For Sale:  Military pricing IS A PRIVILEGE NOT an expectation
location: Everywhere Tacoma South, Southwest Washington, Washington
postcontent:
Listen up all you military or "first responders" out there buying used guns.  As a veteran and an LE professional I say your expectation to buy an LE model from a civilian for LE pricing is very UNREALISTIC.  You have to meet on common grounds.  Civilians don't pay what we do so please stop comparing this special privilege pricing to people who have to pay the new or used retail market pricing.  

We've earned this privilege, but ONLY where we can get it WHEN they have it in stock.  My best friend just told me he feels "we're" taking advantage of this and shared his emails... Whoever this jblm guy is (not going to go there), offering him $350 for a lnib MP9 with 4 mags... Then bashing him when he passed... Shameful.  So please STOP trying to buy mil spec or LE spec guns off of NON military or NON LE for what you "would" pay if it was in stock.  If it's not, you pay what it is where it's at.  Or wait till it's in stock.  

Many of us have fought hard for our country and understand parity, many of us respect this pricing privilege.  For those who want to take advantage of people... Reestablish your true north.

Just my 2 cents.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith & Wesson M&P 15 (M4/AR15 chambered in 5.56)--MUST SEE ($900 OBO)
postcontent:
Like new in original case--yes comes with hard case and all the original paperwork. Gun has been fired, but so little that it shows practically 0 signs of wear. If you are looking for the perfect AR15 at a discounted  price, this is it. 
Smith and Wesson's M&P15 consists of their M4 stamped upper receiver atop their legal-to-own (for civilians) AR15 lower. This particular rifle has the MOE package on it for a comfortable grip, but I will also throw in a spare set of carbine length hand guards, just in case you'd rather have the customizability that comes with a set of aluminum quad-rails. The package also has a magpul flip-up rear sight--allowing for optics to be mounted without the removal of the rear sight. This thing will fire practically any kind of ammunition. 
The M&P 15 is renowned for its unsurpassable reliability and accuracy for a reasonable price, so that anyone can afford a top-shelf rifle, for a mid-shelf price. 
It has been cleaned and lubed with frog lube literally every time it has been out of the case. Even though it has mainly been fired at indoor ranges and never gotten dirty (kept out of the elements/sand/dirt/water/rain/etc), since I am selling I found it necessary for the firearm to be completely stripped and cleaned inside and out for the next owner. 
I will also include riser mount and .223/5.56 calibrated BDC compensation for distance shooting on the rifle (please note the scope has not been sighted in yet ). The scope also has a light up reticle (blue/green/red) with brightness settings to optimize target acquisition, thus decreasing the time in-between followup shots.
Another plus is that not only does it come with the original 30 rd "M&P 15" stamped Pmag, but also includes 3 other 20rd pre-ban mags--which I liked because they do  not hang down as far as the 30rd ones. 
Have a cmmg .22 conversion kit that I can add for an additional $75 ($219 new)--it definitely cuts the cost of shooting and makes it possible to shoot the rifle on a pistol range (some places do not allow high powered rifles). If interested, feel free to inquire about .22lr bullets, as do happen to have some on hand.
Also comes with 2 boxes of 5.56 ammunition.

The rifle has pretty much sat in the safe since I purchased it, as I live in a subdivision and cannot shoot in the back yard--making shooting a hassle (we have land, but it is out of the state), so I cannot justify keeping it.
